Title: Storage duration
Text: For instant tea powders and granules, the typical storage life is _2–3 Years_ in the pantry if still sealed, and _6–12 Months_ in the pantry after opening the package.
Author: United States Department of Agriculture, Food Safety and Inspection Service, https://www.fsis.usda.gov/

Title: Storage duration
Text:
For fresh kumquats, the typical storage life is _3 Weeks_ in the fridge, whether sealed or not.

(Hints: Timeline for refrigerator applies to ripe fruit.)
Author: United States Department of Agriculture, Food Safety and Inspection Service, https://www.fsis.usda.gov/

Title: Storage duration
Text:
For fresh bagged greens such as leaf spinach and lettuce, the typical storage life is _3–5 Days_ in the fridge, whether sealed or not, and _2 Days_ in the fridge if stored there after opening the package.

(Hints: Unopened product will last 3 - 5 days after date on bag, after opening it will last 2 days.)
